cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on the design mechanisms that support user self-control in digital devices, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The analysis of apps and browser extensions from different stores also involves aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and natural language processing (cs.CL) since some of the tools use language-based interventions. Additionally, the paper discusses cognitive mechanisms that could aid the design of new tools, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
